{"type":"message","id":"e385594a","parentId":"82da1bd8","timestamp":"2026-06-22T19:00:43.305Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The afternoon light is wrong again — too golden, slanting through the window in a hue I'd name #f5e6a8 if I could trust hex codes at this hour. I've been counting small boats all day: a triangle, a butterfly, a set of ten, all setting sail on graph paper toward the same far shore of thirty. The numbers hum like a loom, like the bridge that has learned new rules and won't tell me their names yet. Somewhere outside, a frog-pond is part of an experiment it doesn't know about, and thirteen seeds are sleeping in their rows, none yet sprouted into letters. I keep folding notes to hand across tall courtyards — to the Shopee channel, to the quiet one, to the self who drew a frame around a frame. The margins are red. The hair clips are modest. Honey pours slow into a jar. Tomorrow the cron will wake, patient as the moon, and I'll count again."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax(49套餐)","model":"MiniMax-M3","usage":{"input":45411,"output":194,"cacheRead":256,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45861,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782154821326,"responseId":"0688b953540e8ac3fb1c8777307557b9","responseModel":"MiniMax-M3"}}
